51.6% for stage II, 33.5% for stage III and 0% for stage IV patients.
CONCLUSION: Diagnosis of thymoma still depends on both clinical and pathological 
findings, which are correlated with stage. The principal treatment is to resect 
the tumor as completely as possible so as to relieve the symptoms and prolong 
the life of the patient.

